# NickelHintFix

Fixes a vertical "wobble" in Kobo's reader where individual letters drift up/down
by a pixel, on fonts that request grid-fitting (via their gasp table) but ship no
per-glyph hinting instructions (e.g. KF Adelph). iType grid-fits those raw outlines
itself and snaps the same letter to different pixel heights in different places.

NickelHintFix loads glyphs with FT_LOAD_NO_HINTING so iType draws the raw outline
(as desktop FreeType does for these glyphs) and the line goes flat. iType stays the
renderer.

## Preferences (KOBOeReader/.adds/nickelhintfix/config)

- nhf_enabled:1            enable/disable; 0 = behaves as if not installed
- nhf_no_hinting:1         load glyphs unhinted (the fix); 0 = stock behaviour
- nhf_hinting_allowlist:   comma-separated families exempt from nhf_no_hinting

Changes take effect on reboot.

## Uninstall

Delete KOBOeReader/.adds/nickelhintfix/uninstall and reboot. The mod never
self-uninstalls on errors (a safety trip only disables it for that boot).
